    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I beg you would please to give my compliments to <persName ref="pe0192">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Elliot Bookseller</persName> &amp; let him
                    know I am very sorry that I made my arrangements before his application came, or
                    I should have paid it due respect. He must as usual apply to the advertised
                    Booksellers in Town.</p>
                <p>I owe <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> a
                    letter: will soon write to him my thoughts. The public calamities will I fear
                    for a time prove a sad check to our publications.<note type="editorial">Probably
                        a reference to the negative economic climate created by the American
                        Revolutionary War (1775–1783) and its impact on publishing and
                        bookselling.</note> but the studies will serve to beguile the miseries of
                    the times, till better come. So let us pursue our innocent amusements. I beg my
                    best wishes to <persName ref="pe0022">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Ramsay</persName>. I will write to him from <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>.</p>
                <p>I also beg you to thank <persName ref="pe0192">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Elliot</persName> for his kind presents: but wish to pay for them as I am
                    unable to satisfy his wishes. Be so good as to discharge the debt &amp; let me
                    know what it is. perhaps I may serve him in <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low’s</persName> publication.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>Dear Sir <lb/>sincerely y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T. Pennant</persName></signed>

                <dateline>March 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1778</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> next to <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom house</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
